Excellent! Now I have all the information needed. Let me create a comprehensive report by compiling all the findings.

## Command Palette Dialog Configuration Report

Based on my exploration of the IPTVnator codebase, here's the complete configuration for how the command palette dialog is opened and displayed:

### 1. Dialog Open Configuration

**Location:** `/Users/4gray/Code/iptvnator/libs/workspace/shell/feature/src/lib/workspace-shell/services/workspace-shell.facade.ts` (lines 768-794)

```typescript
openCommandPalette(): void {
    const dialogRef = this.dialog.open<
        WorkspaceCommandPaletteComponent,
        { commands: WorkspaceCommandItem[]; query: string },
        WorkspaceCommandSelection | undefined
    >(WorkspaceCommandPaletteComponent, {
        width: 'min(760px, 92vw)',
        maxWidth: '92vw',
        panelClass: 'workspace-command-palette-overlay',
        autoFocus: false,
        data: {
            commands: this.getCommandPaletteItems(),
            query: this.searchQuery(),
        },
    });
    // ... dialog result handling
}
```

**Dialog Config Properties:**
- `width`: `'min(760px, 92vw)'` - responsive width, max 760px or 92% viewport width
- `maxWidth`: `'92vw'` - constrains maximum width to 92% viewport width
- `panelClass`: `'workspace-command-palette-overlay'` - custom CSS class for overlay styling
- `autoFocus`: `false` - prevents auto-focus to allow controlled focus management
- `data`: Passes commands list and query string to the component

---

### 2. Global Overlay Styles

**Location:** `/Users/4gray/Code/iptvnator/apps/web/src/styles.scss` (lines 115-124)

```scss
.cdk-overlay-backdrop {
    backdrop-filter: blur(4px);
}

// Full-screen overlay dialogs (global search/recent) must stay interactive in Electron.
.global-search-overlay,
.global-search-overlay .mat-mdc-dialog-surface,
.global-search-overlay .mat-mdc-dialog-container {
    app-region: no-drag;
}
```

**Key Styles:**
- **CDK Overlay Backdrop**: Applies `backdrop-filter: blur(4px)` - creates a glass-morphism effect with 4px blur on the backdrop
- **Global Search Overlay**: Contains `app-region: no-drag` (Electron-specific) to keep dialogs interactive in the desktop app

**Command Palette Specific Overlay Style:**

**Location:** `/Users/4gray/Code/iptvnator/libs/workspace/shell/feature/src/lib/workspace-shell/workspace-shell.component.scss` (lines 187-191)

```scss
:host ::ng-deep .workspace-command-palette-overlay .mat-mdc-dialog-surface {
    background: transparent;
    box-shadow: none;
    overflow: visible;
}
```

**Purpose:**
- Makes the Material dialog surface transparent (the component itself provides the background)
- Removes Material's default box shadow
- Allows overflow visibility for the dialog content

---

### 3. Theme Variables

**Location:** `/Users/4gray/Code/iptvnator/apps/web/src/m3-theme.scss`

The app uses Material Design 3 (M3) themes with custom CSS variables. The variables are defined on the `html` root element and are theme-aware (light/dark).

**Light Theme Variables (lines 51-112):**
```scss
--app-shell-bg: #eef0f3;
--app-rail-bg: #eef0f3;
--app-header-bg: #eef0f3;
--app-content-bg: #f5f6f8;
--app-on-surface: #1d1b1e;
--app-hover-overlay: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.06);
--app-search-bg: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.7);
--app-search-border: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
--app-selection-color: #2f7bff;
--app-selection-on-color: #eef4ff;
--app-selection-surface: color-mix(in srgb, var(--app-selection-color) 14%, transparent);
--app-selection-surface-strong: color-mix(in srgb, var(--app-selection-color) 22%, transparent);
--app-selection-border: color-mix(in srgb, var(--app-selection-color) 52%, transparent);
--app-selection-glow: color-mix(in srgb, var(--app-selection-color) 34%, transparent);
--app-widget-bg: #ffffff;
--app-widget-header-bg: #fafbfc;
```

**Dark Theme Variables (lines 122-186):**
```scss
--app-shell-bg: #0d0f12;
--app-rail-bg: #111318;
--app-header-bg: #111318;
--app-content-bg: #161a22;
--app-on-surface: #e6e1e5;
--app-hover-overlay: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.08);
--app-search-bg: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.05);
--app-search-border: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.09);
--app-selection-color: #78adff;
--app-selection-on-color: #071225;
--app-selection-surface: color-mix(in srgb, var(--app-selection-color) 18%, transparent);
--app-selection-surface-strong: color-mix(in srgb, var(--app-selection-color) 28%, transparent);
--app-selection-border: color-mix(in srgb, var(--app-selection-color) 62%, transparent);
--app-selection-glow: color-mix(in srgb, var(--app-selection-color) 44%, transparent);
--app-widget-bg: #1e2330;
--app-widget-header-bg: #232840;
```

**Material Design 3 System Variables:** The app also uses Material's built-in M3 variables like:
- `--mat-sys-surface`
- `--mat-sys-on-surface`
- `--mat-sys-outline-variant`
- `--mat-sys-primary`
- `--mat-sys-surface-container-*`

These are defined by Material's theme configuration in `m3-theme.scss` and are auto-generated based on the selected palette (violet primary, cyan tertiary).

---

### 4. Command Palette Component Styles

**Location:** `/Users/4gray/Code/iptvnator/libs/workspace/shell/feature/src/lib/workspace-command-palette/workspace-command-palette.component.scss`

The component uses the theme variables defined above:
- **Palette Shell**: Uses `--app-header-bg` for background and Material border colors
- **Search Input**: Uses `--app-search-bg` and `--app-search-border` for styling
- **Command Items**: Use `--app-selection-surface`, `--app-selection-surface-strong`, and `--app-selection-border` for hover/selected states
- **Command Icons**: Use `--app-selection-color` for the accent color

Max height constraint: `max-height: 80vh` with results scrollable up to `min(56vh, 520px)`

---

### 5. Theme Application System

**Location:** `/Users/4gray/Code/iptvnator/apps/web/src/app/services/settings.service.ts`

